            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>garam masala </strong>and <strong>cayenne pepper </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>chopped paneer</strong> and cook for 4-6 min or until charred slightly, turning occasionally for even colouring</p><p>Once done, set the <strong>spiced paneer </strong>aside<strong> </strong>and reserve the pan</p>",
